### Client Setup (Installing React Application)

Follow the steps below to set up the React client for the **Cab Booking Application** using **Vite**.

#### Step 1: Open the Client Folder

Open the **client** folder in the Visual Studio Code terminal.

#### Step 2: Create a React Application Using Vite

Run the following command to create a new React project:

```bash
npm create vite@latest . -- --template react
```

When prompted, select the following options:

**Framework:**

```text
React
```

**Variant:**

```text
JavaScript
```

#### Step 3: Navigate to the Client Directory

If you are not already inside the client folder, run:

```bash
cd client
```

#### Step 4: Install Project Dependencies

Install all the required packages by running:

```bash
npm install
```

#### Step 5: Start the Development Server

Launch the React development server with:

```bash
npm run dev
```

After the server starts successfully, Vite will display a local development URL similar to:

```text
VITE vX.X.X ready in XXX ms

➜  Local:   http://localhost:5173/
➜  Network: http://192.xxx.x.x:5173/
```

Open the **Local** URL in your web browser to view the React application.

